    "instructions": "1. Identify the universal scaling-critical exponent (often denoted in terms of the regularity threshold or the critical Sobolev space index) for dissipative PDEs with diffusion order 's' in dimension 'n'. Focus on the scaling-invariant norm or the regularity threshold $\\alpha$ such that the equation is critical under $u_\\lambda(x,t) = \\lambda^\\alpha u(\\lambda x, \\lambda^{2s} t)$. \n2. Express this exponent clearly as a function of $n$ and $s$. \n3. Systematically apply this formula to verify consistency with: \n   - 3D Navier-Stokes (n=3, s=1)\n   - 2D Navier-Stokes (n=2, s=1)\n   - 1D Burgers (n=1, s=1)\n   - Surface Quasi-Geostrophic (SQG) equations (identify n and s, typically n=2, s=1/2 for critical)\n   - Magnetohydrodynamics (MHD) (identify n and s)\n   - Fractional Navier-Stokes (n=3, s in (0,1))\n4. Provide a rigorous step-by-step verification for each case, ensuring the scaling analysis matches the identified exponent.",
